eedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Mai 20, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104mlz1665702717675.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mlz1665702717675.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mlz1665702717675.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"mlz1665702717675\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specify the maximum number of requests a shared Uniface server can execute.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"mlz1665702717675__section_w67ab1b5b1_w68ab1b5_w69ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mlz1665702717675__p_d139178e1_d139179e1_d139180e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/maxreq</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">MaxRequests</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"mlz1665702717675__section_gjv_bmr_zvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d892643e64\">Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mlz1665702717675__p_d139184e1_d139185e1_d139186e1\">Use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/maxreq</span> switch in the\n        [SERVERS] section of the Uniface Router assignment file <span class=\"ph filepath\">urouter.asn</span> to\n        specify the maximum number of requests that a shared server, identified by its server name\n        (UST), is allowed to execute. The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/maxreq</span> switch has meaning only for a\n        shared server.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mlz1665702717675__p_d139187e1_d139188e1_d139189e1\">The server will be stopped only if the following\n        conditions, corresponding to the server’s role, are true:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"mlz1665702717675__ul_jlk_dmr_zvb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mlz1665702717675__li_d49052e1_d49053e1_d49054e1\">No open files </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mlz1665702717675__li_d49055e1_d49056e1_d49057e1\">No open database transactions </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mlz1665702717675__li_d49058e1_d49059e1_d49060e1\">No open component instances </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mlz1665702717675__p_d139190e1_d139191e1_d139192e1\">If omitted, the default value is -1, meaning an\n        unlimited number. If you specify <code class=\"ph codeph\">/maxreq=0</code>, the server will never be\n        started and an error will be sent to the client. This can be used to disable certain servers\n        for maintenance.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/luh1665702694600.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>urouter.sh</a><p>Unix script for starting the Uniface Router.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529978\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529978\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "/maxreq Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Mai 20, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Specify the maximum number of requests a shared Uniface server can execute. /maxreq = MaxRequests Description Use the /maxreq switch in the [SERVERS] section of the Uniface Router assignment file urouter.asn to specify the maximum number of requests that a shared server, identified by its server name (UST), is allowed to execute. The /maxreq switch has meaning only for a shared server. The server will be stopped only if the following conditions, corresponding to the server’s role, are true: No open files No open database transactions No open component instances If omitted, the default value is -1, meaning an unlimited number. If you specify /maxreq=0 , the server will never be started and an error will be sent to the client. This can be used to disable certain servers for maintenance. Related Links urouter.sh Unix script for starting the Uniface Router. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}